Key Match Events: The Magic was overwhelmed by the starpower of the Timberwolves without Banchero, Suggs, and Wagner.
Pre-Game Insights: The Magic had to wait at least one more game before the return of All-Star forward Paolo Banchero on Thursday night.
Post-Match Reflections: Without Banchero, Suggs, and Wagner, Orlando was overwhelmed by the starpower of the Timberwolves.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Guided by two-time All-NBA forward Julius Randle (23 points), All-NBA guard Anthony Edwards (21), four-time defensive player of the year Rudy Gobert (15 rebounds).
Others: Dwight Howard claims Adam Silver called him after he tweeted ‘Free Palestine’; NBA says that’s ‘categorically false’.
